    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="1827"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1827">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 816.001/7.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Minister of Salvador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Salvador</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 30, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to inform your excellency
                    that on yesterday Senor Don Carlos Melendez delivered, as required by our
                    political Constitution, the Presidency of the Republic to First Designado Dr.
                    Don Alfonso Quiñónez, who will discharge its duties until the 1st of March of
                    the coming year 1915, the time set by law for the induction into the Chief
                    Magistracy of the citizen who is elected at the Presidential elections that will
                    begin on the second Sunday of January next.</p>
                <p>Asking your excellency kindly to take note of the foregoing,</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Francisco Dueñas</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
